{'name': 'Nikka Ramen', 'address': '5701 Calle Real', 'city': 'Goleta', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Restaurants, Japanese, Ramen', 'hours': {'Tuesday': '17:0-21:30', 'Wednesday': '17:0-21:30', 'Thursday': '17:0-21:30', 'Friday': '17:0-21:30', 'Saturday': '17:0-21:30', 'Sunday': '17:0-21:30'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'touristy': False, 'hipster': None, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': True, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 4.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-19 06:15:16', 'review_text': "Amazing place, great food , great location. The atmosphere was fun, the music was great. I can tell it's a very popular spot. Servers are very attentive. I will definitely go back again."}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-18 01:53:38', 'review_text': "Officially my favorite ramen spot. We don't live in the area but now make it a point to stop by and satisfy our Nikka craving whenever we're in Goleta.

The gyoza was a yummy appetizer but the spicy tuna was sooooo goood! I could eat 10 of those! The basic pork tonkatsu was just as delicious as I remember. Al dente noodles and broth cooked to perfection. The pork chashu is A1 quality. Every ingredient was meant to be on that plate from the tender pork chunks to the salad to the soft boiled egg.

We love Nikka. Period."}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-07 01:34:51', 'review_text': 'Holly F@ck... mind blowing. Literally spent the last 20 minutes of my life having a mouth gasm. My knees are weak, And ima little sweaty. This ramen just had its way with me.... and I liked it'}]}

{'name': 'Panino', 'address': '5666 Calle Real', 'city': 'Goleta', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Sandwiches, Delis, Restaurants, Soup, Salad, Food', 'hours': {'Monday': '10:0-16:0', 'Tuesday': '10:0-16:0', 'Wednesday': '10:0-16:0', 'Thursday': '10:0-16:0', 'Friday': '10:0-16:0', 'Saturday': '10:0-16:0', 'Sunday': '11:0-15:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'no', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 3.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2021-04-22 19:38:05', 'review_text': "Okay, this was not exactly what I expected, but its a delightful surprise!! I decided to try something new and go with the English Stilton and pear sandwich today...I don't know why, but I assumed the cranberries and walnuts would be in a kind of chutney so when I opened my sandwich I was kind of disappointed until I took a bite. HOLY COW ITS DELICIOUS! Everyone should try this sandwich on Foccacia bread!

Classic faves of mine also include the Turkey and Salami, Cobb Salad Sandwich, and Caprese Sandwich. I've honestly never had anything that I didn't like. Thanks for another delicious lunch today, Panino!"}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2021-01-27 23:52:51', 'review_text': 'A couple of months ago my wife and I had to do some business in Goleta. When we were done we asked where we could get a good sandwich. They recommended Panino. It was great!! Today my wife and I were bored from staying at home cause of the pandemic. We decided to take a drive to Goleta and have lunch at Panino. Again, our sandwiches/lunch were great. Very friendly and good service. Take it from us who drive all the way from Oxnard. Highly recommended!!'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2020-12-04 04:09:52', 'review_text': "Depending on my taste buds for the day, Panino has either the best or the 2nd best sandwich in town. That would be the Italian combo on focaccia. Layered with fine meats and cheeses, it's thoughtfully complemented by a delightful basil aioli, lettuce, and thin cut green bell pepper and cucumber. If one maneuvers the meat and cheese correctly, every bite has the most appealing ratio of ingredients you will ever taste in a sandwich. It's like taking a bite out of the Sistine Chapel, or being able to taste the Mona Lisa. If they ever change it, I will seriously write a strongly worded letter to management. 

If I ever were to try any of their other sandwiches, I'm assuming they would also be delicious. The prices are a bit more than average, much as the price of a Lakers ticket costs more than one for the Clippers."}]}

{'name': "Mony's Mexican Food", 'address': '217 E Anacapa St', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Restaurants, Mexican', 'hours': {'Monday': '10:30-15:30', 'Tuesday': '10:30-15:30', 'Wednesday': '10:30-15:30', 'Thursday': '10:30-15:30', 'Friday': '10:30-15:30', 'Saturday': '10:30-15:30'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': None, 'WiFi': 'no', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': False, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'touristy': False, 'hipster': None, 'romantic': False, 'divey': None, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': None, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 4.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-17 22:50:16', 'review_text': 'All four of us had an amazing experience. Guacamole is the thicker rather than creamy. More so a pico de gallo con guacamole. 

Burrito had some great fresh rice and beans! 

Give a try of the mole and mango salsa. We went back for more!'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-08 21:08:38', 'review_text': 'The tacos tasted unbelievably good, there was so much flavor in them which was the highlight.'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2021-12-21 04:00:13', 'review_text': 'Best tacos and salsa bar in SB. Very reasonable too, friendly staff. Avocado salsa is so yummy.'}]}

{'name': "Anna's Marketplace Bakery", 'address': '7018 Marketplace Dr', 'city': 'Goleta', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Donuts, Restaurants, Bakeries, Food, Sandwiches', 'hours': {'Monday': '0:0-0:0', 'Tuesday': '6:0-17:30', 'Wednesday': '6:0-17:30', 'Thursday': '6:0-16:0', 'Friday': '6:0-17:30', 'Saturday': '6:0-17:30', 'Sunday': '6:0-16:30'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'no', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}}, 'business_stars': 4.0, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-18 01:20:49', 'review_text': 'Donuts are delish, nice and light and fresh. The chocolate croissant was really good as well! They are a little more pricey than some donut shops but have really good flavor.'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2022-01-01 18:44:53', 'review_text': "Happy 2022 everyone! This year will surely see me at Anna's quite a few more times. When a friend told me that a bakery close to where I live offers vegan donuts, I was psyched--I'm vegan and it's oddly difficult to find good vegan food, sweets, and drinks in this area. Checking out Anna's Bakery a few days later, I wasn't let down. 

I've sampled both the vegan glazed donut and the apple fritter, as well as the house coffee, and all were great. The donut is puffy and airy and sweet. The fritter has glorious crunchy, oily edges and a surprisingly doughy interior, complete with apple pieces and a glossy, sugary varnish. (Did you know some 'apple fritters' elsewhere don't even contain apple?) The coffee is hot and black and perfectly balances the candy-like sweetness of the baked goods. 

There's always a long line and seating is limited so be prepared. This shop also offers non-vegan donuts (the majority contain milk products, though I'm crossing my fingers for a vegan cake donut in 2022). There is also a menu of savory food. Breads and donuts and cookies are also available to go. That pink box, unmistakably brimming with tasty treats, is sure to being smiles to any gathering... especially if you have vegan friends who are so used to being left out when sweet baked goods appear."}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2021-10-27 05:28:12', 'review_text': "SO friendly and donuts are always amazing. All staff, from the cashier to the owner. All lovely people. They always greet with by my name. I love to see how they interact with all customers. I am always happy to give them business as it is very well deserved. Keep up the wonderful work! Anna's has been around for a long time and has always been one of my favorites."}]}

{'name': 'Bougainvillea', 'address': '202 State St, Ste A', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Food, Restaurants, Beer, Wine & Spirits, Italian, Pizza', 'hours': {'Monday': '11:0-10:0', 'Tuesday': '11:0-10:0', 'Wednesday': '11:0-10:0', 'Thursday': '11:0-10:0', 'Friday': '11:0-10:0', 'Saturday': '11:0-10:0', 'Sunday': '11:0-10:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': True, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': None, 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': None}, 'business_stars': 4.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2009-05-31 00:18:23', 'review_text': 'what a bummer!!! I was so excited to have dinner here and there are huge "for rent" signs in the windows. It will be missed.'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2008-08-26 03:30:05', 'review_text': 'My husband and I went here tonight and the food and service was excellent.  He had the deep dish barbecue pizza and I had the ravioli.  The food was delicious.  The service was also very accommodating.  We highly recommend this place.'}, {'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2008-05-29 04:33:08', 'review_text': "Atmosphere is very nice here! They have a semi-separate area with a fire place that was great for an anniversary celebration with my girl. Wine list is decent but I felt they didn't offer enough wines by the glass. Food was just good (7 out of 10). She had the Salmon special of the day which was average. I had the Chicken Vesuvio which I really liked. I wanted to try the local wines so I had the Santa Barbara Syrah and she had the S.B. Chardonnay. Both were reasonably priced and well worth it!

Total for the night was $65 for two entrees, two glasses of wine, and Tiramisu (which was excellent).

Highly recommended for a nice place to have dinner. Would've been 5 stars if the food was better."}]}

{'name': 'California Wood-Fired Catering', 'address': '', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Food Trucks, Event Planning & Services, Pizza, Restaurants, Caterers, Food', 'hours': None, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': None, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': None, 'WiFi': None, 'RestaurantsTakeOut': False, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}}, 'business_stars': 4.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2015-05-24 00:32:27', 'review_text': 'We had them provide pizza for about 100 folks at Municipal Wine. Food was great -- salad, pizza, and gelato. All great. 

They warned us that it would be hard to get pizzas out for that large a crowd, and they were right. But they did the best they could in the situation and everyone was happy. Their chefs worked hard to please and did a great job. 

Only negatives were: underestimated salad, so we ran out a little early. And Email response was a little slow. That said, a pleasure to work with and tasty food!'}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2013-07-25 22:35:25', 'review_text': 'California Wood-Fired Catering is delicious and perfect for a casual, fun event! I have had the pleasure of working with them many times for events at the private event venue that I manage. While I have heard from a few clients that the owner can be sometimes difficult to get a hold of, I myself have never had a problem reaching him by calling the number listed on their website. Either way they always come through with the events that they book and the guests always rave about how fun it is having a wood-fired burning oven popping out fresh pizzas as well as how delicious the food is.'}, {'review_stars': 3.0, 'review_date': '2013-07-06 04:21:37', 'review_text': 'This year for 4th of July we checked out the Stow House old fashioned 4th of July:) What a pleasant surprise. We were lucky enough to stumble on these pizza people who were making pizza in special oven:) it was really good and hope they can come to our school carnivals next year:)'}]}

{'name': 'Union Ale', 'address': '214 State St', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Bars, American (Traditional), Restaurants, Cocktail Bars, Nightlife', 'hours': {'Monday': '11:0-23:0', 'Tuesday': '11:0-23:0', 'Wednesday': '11:0-23:0', 'Thursday': '11:0-23:0', 'Friday': '11:0-23:0', 'Saturday': '11:0-23:0', 'Sunday': '11:0-23:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'no', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 3.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 2.0, 'review_date': '2016-09-23 22:32:27', 'review_text': "2nd transformation in 18 months...same owners, but now it feels like there's even less on the menu, and it's even more disorganized. What remains arrives without salad or fries or even a tidbit of  garnish. Your food comes on a metal tray without napkins or eating tools. If you order a hamburger, expect it to come under a super greasy bun. 

The patio is no longer covered so you'll be sitting in direct sunlight. It feels like this place is having an extended identity crisis. 

Damn if the funk zone doesn't need some decent dependable lunch places. This establishment is really missing out on an easy opportunity here. Great location, nice facility, but no thought or care in what they're serving up or in what they want to be."}, {'review_stars': 2.0, 'review_date': '2016-01-10 02:25:11', 'review_text': "Horrible service. It took 20 minutes to get a drink order when it wasn't even that busy. Their food is goods"}, {'review_stars': 2.0, 'review_date': '2016-01-04 20:55:40', 'review_text': "2 stars for the beer choices which is the only positive remnant of what was one of my go to places downtown. They've all but eliminated all the great food they served. They've now removed all but 2 TVs. Very disappointing business choices. I walked in this past weekend to catch a nationally televised hockey game, something I've done dozens of times here in the past. The bartender acknowledges us but is so busy covering the entire restaurant that he didn't get to us for nearly 10 minutes. We had to walk out and find a more suitable place to catch the game. Can't say I'll have a desire to go back. This town was already lacking decent sports bars with a good beer selection."}]}

{'name': 'Casa Blanca Restaurant', 'address': '330 State St', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Mexican, Restaurants, Seafood', 'hours': {'Monday': '16:0-22:0', 'Tuesday': '16:0-22:0', 'Wednesday': '16:0-22:0', 'Thursday': '16:0-22:0', 'Friday': '16:0-0:0', 'Saturday': '10:0-0:0', 'Sunday': '10:0-22:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': True, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': True, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 3.5, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2020-03-11 05:59:08', 'review_text': "My friend and I came here for lunch on Saturday. I am not sure how it is at dinner, but for lunch there was no line so it was fast to get a table. The waiter was very thorough and accommodating. Both my friend and I had the blood orange margarita, which was so good because it had a jalapeÃ±o kick! But, don't worry it's not too spicy for anyone that is sensitive to spice, it was just right. 

We both ended up going with the combination plate; me the taco and enchilada and her the taco and tamale. To be honest the only reason why I didn't go with the mahi mahi taco was because it was singular (taco) versus the other tacos were plural in the name (tacos) and so I was expecting to get at least two tacos in the combo. However, only one came so I would ask that the menu be more clear. But, the food was delicious and we even had enough for leftovers. Both plates came with rice and beans too. 

There is an axxess deal for BOGO entree for lunch or dinner as well. So with all the food and drinks we had my friend and I were able to split it evenly for about $24 per person, which I think is a great deal for such a quality food."}, {'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2020-03-08 15:09:08', 'review_text': "Delicious food and drinks! Really fast service. Nice location with a nice scenic patio. They have heaters so you don't have to worry about getting cold. I ordered the burrito and my husband got the fajitas, both were delicious! I also got the margarita flight, which I highly recommend. If you're close to Amtrak on state, I would recommend stopping by!"}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2020-03-01 05:02:35', 'review_text': 'Ate at the bar tonight for my friends birthday. The bartender Dan, (tall, light and handsome) was attentive and took great care of us! Fast drinks with a warm welcoming personality, a great guy. Good food too! my Bf and I had the tacos.. simple but tasty! Thank you!'}]}

{'name': 'Left At Albuquerque', 'address': '700 State St', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Tex-Mex, Restaurants', 'hours': None, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': None, 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': None}, 'business_stars': 3.0, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2010-01-13 20:29:31', 'review_text': 'Was here visiting from out of town. Stayed for most of happy hour a couple days. killer margaritas. And huge selection of tequilas too. 

The reason I gave it a great review is they had an appetizer I have never been able to find anywhere else. It was called "Ball of Fire" "For people that like really hot or just plain lunatics" It was a Habanero Popper. Like a jalapeno popper but WAYYYYY hotter. It was fun trying to cool off with more beer or margaritas. Thank God we had a ride back home. Anyhow great memory & we really enjoyed the chips and salsa & the happy hours.'}, {'review_stars': 1.0, 'review_date': '2009-10-05 21:23:14', 'review_text': 'It was all wrong from the moment I asked if we could sit at the bar to have an appetizer and drinks, and the girl that was seating us said, "yes," but we must order an appetizer.  Then she proceeded to take us out to the patio which confused me because I asked for the bar, but I dismissed that.  She sat us at a table, and we ordered our appetizer and drinks from the server.  He comes back with our drinks and explains that they may ask us to move inside because the patio is reserved for customers ordering dinners rather than just appetizers and drinks.  The patio was not full at all, and we told him we were told that we could order an appetizer alone, but still he said we may have to move later as that is the rule.  No apologies at all.  Ugh - I wanted to leave right after his comment...but I figured I should have my beer first.   First, we never asked to be seated outside; second, if that is a rule at the restaurant, why did they seat us outside when we specifically asked for the bar and told the seater that we were only ordering appetizer and drinks?  

Oh, the appetizer was not so great, but we didn't order anything fancy.  It's possible their other food is really good though.  The server spilled my beer on my sunglasses :( .  We quickly had our drinks and appetizer, paid, then got out of there.'}, {'review_stars': 3.0, 'review_date': '2009-09-23 21:14:27', 'review_text': 'Great outdoor patio area.  Loved the ambiance.  The chips and salsa are good, food was okay.  Nothing special.'}]}

{'name': 'Muddy Waters Cafe', 'address': '508 E Haley St', 'city': 'Santa Barbara', 'state': 'CA', 'categories': 'Jazz & Blues, Music Venues, Arts & Entertainment, Nightlife, Restaurants, Bars, Local Flavor, Bagels, Food, Beer, Wine & Spirits, Dive Bars, Delis, Coffee & Tea', 'hours': {'Monday': '6:0-18:0', 'Tuesday': '6:0-18:0', 'Wednesday': '6:0-18:0', 'Thursday': '6:0-18:0', 'Friday': '6:0-18:0', 'Saturday': '8:0-18:0'}, 'attributes': {'BusinessParking': {'garage': False, 'street': True, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}, 'RestaurantsReservations': False, 'OutdoorSeating': True, 'WiFi': 'free', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': True, 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': True, 'Music': None, 'Ambience': {'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}}, 'business_stars': 4.0, 'review_info': [{'review_stars': 4.0, 'review_date': '2015-09-18 02:36:39', 'review_text': "So sad to hear Muddy's is closing . Great coffee house, eclectic art and people! Not sure where my go to place will be now......"}, {'review_stars': 5.0, 'review_date': '2015-08-09 20:19:08', 'review_text': 'So many little spaces, rooms, and nooks to sit on a chair, couch or table.  Perfect for working, meeting up with friends, hanging out.  Great inside and outside space.  Art focused, which I LOVE!

If I lived closer, this would be a regular spot.'}, {'review_stars': 3.0, 'review_date': '2015-05-29 06:16:17', 'review_text': 'Decent coffee at an okay price. Some people like the decorations but I thought it was kind of messy and had a grandma-esque vibe too it. 

I got my usual, an iced coffee and HOT DAMN. It was strong...like a too strong for my tastes. I will come back to try their other drinks though. Not giving up on this place just yet!'}]}
